		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    The Answer to the Stats question on fighters.</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:PeacemakerOC@email.com">Drakiez </a> | 
		            10/14/1999 5:13:10 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">I've figured out that big question on which stat is more important for Class/Race issue. Through playing alot and dueling I've found what is the better stats for people to start with. For the most important Stats,they need to have 100 points(or as close as you can get it to 100) for your character to be good and some stats are more important then others.I've found that AGI isn't more important then STR,DEX for alot of characters. If your Dueling and One person has high AGI and which in turn gives them high AC and the other has high STR. The one with the higher STR is still going to hit the one with the high AGI hard because the person had high enough STR to get past the AC,but the one with the lower STR wont make it past the AC enough(Will hit more but not enough to make a difference).<BR>
-The way you should make your player is<BR>
&gt;If your Character starts with STR of 100 or more(Barbarion,Dwarf,Orge,Troll)then you need to focus on there AGI and DEX. First make sure your DEX is high enough(hopefully 85) and if it doens't start near 85, try and get it close. Then check if AGI is close to 85 and fix if needed. Also if neither are close,devide your bonus points between them.<BR>
<BR>
I've figured out what all the STR does for races with low INT. It makes them hit as hard with there Weapons at there Skill level as some weaker class would at a higher skill lvl. This in effect makes your skill level for that weapon level up to reach the skill level where the damage your hitting for should fit. This effect keeps on going until your skill gets close to Master, when is slows down very much. Classes that don't have a problem with learning skills(Dark-elf,High-elf,Erudite)should be ok with there STR in the mid 80's(85+) to 90's.<BR>
*A special thing on Rogues* If your DEX and AGI are 100(or if you have a Dark-Elf Rogue-90+)you should invest in some STR so you will be abit more affective(only rogue of the same level that could dent my Barbarion Warrior I use was a Half-elf,because of there base STR of 85).<BR>
<BR>
Basically I've founded out that if your Fighter Characters Stats are made right(you put your bonus points in the right place),you will have completely no trouble in playing or leveling up right from the beginning. Some characters will do good no matter how where they put there bonus points(example would be the Race/Class/Deity Combo= Low difficulty). With exception to the Dark races that get hard rating just because of there Race and Deity, any class with Low can put there Bouns points anywhere(Some places are WAY better then others and putting your Bonus points in the right place makes it that much more easier) and any class with Moderate need to put there bonus points in the right place for there character to succeed. -So if your fighter character is to hard to play from the beginning then he's just missing the right amount of STR(Try it and you'll see. Make a Monk with all bonus points in DEX and AGI and leave STR alone, then make one with all bonus points in STR see which one levels the fastest and kills the fastest).<BR>
<BR>
Just thought I'd save you all the time I put into over 6 different characters(Just so you know all the 6 are lvl 10 and up). Also when you can get 2levels in between 5-6hours with a character of STR lower then 80-85 and all DEX and AGI give me a call.<BR>
<BR>
Drakiez <BR>
-Quellious-<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Added by Drakiez<BR>
<BR>
-About that Half-Elf Rogue I was talking about,His base Stats wheren't 85. It was 85 after he added in Bonus points. -And about the 2 levels in 5-6hours, thats was with my barbarion warrior from lvl 10 to my current lvl of 19(also part of this is from my knowlegde of where EXP is best for my current lvl). <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
The time was less at lower lvls for( I had FS 2h'er at lvl 6 since they don't sell for to much and I still have it at lvl 19 and i'm doing just fine killing things). With my barbarion at lvl 19 with my crappy FS 2h'er(crapy for what I could have), I can kill a blue DW caimen or Croc before it gets me past half HP and go find another Blue right afterward and get it alittle after I go beserk.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
- With my monk I find that is almost unfairly easy to kill and lvl(I put all my points into STR after my research and since it reached 100STR it's way easy to kill). Oh and at lvl 3,which i got in 1hr or 2(while doing the Monk Quest in Freeport)my monk was hiting for 10 already and my skill was going up very fast to make up with my hitting ability which proved my reseach right.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
