			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Be careful ....<BR>
<BR>
Strength always helps at low levels... its given. One or two more points of damage is a ton, when the creatures you are fighting only have 20 hp or less.<BR>
<BR>
But when your fighting creatures with 1000+ hps, doing even 5-10 more damage, because of high strength per hit, will make a difference.. but then, realize that while you can do this enhanced damage overall, you could have put some points into agility and maybe avoided a fourth more hits, which is quite a bit once they start hitting for 50+ a smack. Then again... watch dexterity. What is even +50 more damage from strength, if you only land a few hits, here and there...<BR>
<BR>
Yes, strength helps extremely at low levels, but at higher levels, its just a nicety, but not nearly as important as it seemed.<BR>
<BR>
Onigami Satsugai<BR>
Monk of the Ashen Order
